newsitem.title: USA: Most IMM currencies end higher on profit taking.
newsitem.headline: Most IMM currencies end higher on profit taking.

text.p: Most IMM currency futures closed a thinly traded session higher, but the profit taking from the sell side that fueled their advance is expected to be short-lived, traders and analysts said.

"The dollar seems to finding resistance which kicked it off its high, but not down. It's holding very firmly," George Tzanetatos, vice president at Merrill Lynch, said about the dollar's decline to 1.5868 spot during U.S. dealings.
March marks rose to the dollar-low equivalent of $0.6328, punching through a minor resistance level of $0.6306 at midsession. One firm alone bought 450 March marks at $0.6290.
